UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0022199682900721
AB  - This paper tries to resolve a problem of stability in portfolio-balance models of the exchange rate. The problem is shown to dissolve if we introduce a few practical considerations relating to deviations from the law of one price, costs of converting currencies and costs of issuing debts in foreign denominations. In addition, the paper develops a new argument for stability of the exchange rate on the spot market based on the transactions demand for money.
