AB  - The paper introduces factor quality considerations into a Heckscher-Ohlin framework and examines the importance of factor skills in determining a country's production pattern and income distribution. Furthermore, factor price equalization between countries with similar but not identical factors is discussed and conditions for international factor migration are developed.
